A convenient enemy would be Canada or Mexico <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
&quot;As for much to gain and little to lose&quot;-who would fight a war, or enter into any situation politically, diplomatically or militarily for that matter, where they had little to gain and a lot to lose???  What a completely meaningless, insepid statement.<br>
<br>
As for news outlets bad mouthing Canada I have yet to hear anyone do so on any stations I've listened to.  Perhaps you should attempt to switch channels?  I would think that entering into a bold initiative to switch channels would be one of those situations where you would have the potential to gain a lot and lose little.<br>
<br>
As for propaganda I agree with you.  I prefer a little more truth in my diet and it sickens me to play up that aspect when the real concern to the US is Saddam's threat to the US.  However, that doesn't make the other items any less true.<br>
